# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# THIS FILE IS NOT LOADED AT RUNTIME.
# It's a reference for the `npx convex env set ...` commands you need
# to run once. Convex stores its env vars on the server, not in a file.
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─── Kick OAuth app (from https://kick.com/settings/developer) ─────────────
# Scopes: user:read  channel:read  events:subscribe
# Redirect URL: https://<YOUR-DEPLOYMENT>.convex.site/auth/kick/callback
# Webhook URL:  https://<YOUR-DEPLOYMENT>.convex.site/webhooks/kick
#
#   npx convex env set KICK_CLIENT_ID     <your client id>
#   npx convex env set KICK_CLIENT_SECRET <your client secret>

# ─── Crypto keys (run `node scripts/generate-keys.mjs` once) ───────────────
# The script prints four `npx convex env set ...` commands — run all four:
#   JWT_PRIVATE_JWK, JWT_PUBLIC_JWK, API_HMAC_KEY, TOKEN_ENCRYPTION_KEY

# ─── Extension allowlist (your unpacked extension ID) ──────────────────────
# Find it at chrome://extensions after `pnpm --filter @kick-crates/extension dev`.
# Include the dev ID and (later) the published Web Store ID, comma-separated.
#
#   npx convex env set ALLOWED_EXTENSION_IDS <your-ext-id>

# ─── Auto-provided by Convex (you do NOT set these) ────────────────────────
# CONVEX_SITE_URL   - the https://<deployment>.convex.site URL
# CONVEX_CLOUD_URL  - the https://<deployment>.convex.cloud URL

# ─── Verify everything is set ──────────────────────────────────────────────
#   npx convex env list
